RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coextend
<hw>Co`ex*tend</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Coextended</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Coextending</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To extend through the same
space or time with another; to extend to the same degree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>According to which the least body may be <qex>coextended</qex>
with the greatest.</q> <rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Has your English language one single word that is
<qex>coextended</qex> through all these significations?</q>
<rj><qau>Bentley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 275 --></p>

<p><ent>Coextension</ent>⟦br⟧
